<h2>Game Basics</h2>

<h4>Turns</h4>
<p>
  Empires is a turn-based game — each turn represents one month of in-game time.
  You accumulate turns over time and spend them to advance the game.
  The maximum number of stored turns is <%= @game.max_turns %>.
  New turns arrive every <%= @game.seconds_per_turn / 60 %> minutes.
</p>
<p>
  When you end a turn, all production runs, armies move, buildings advance in the queue,
  explorers return, and resources are consumed. The calendar starts at year 1000 A.D.
</p>

<h4>Land</h4>
<p>There are three types of land, each used for different buildings:</p>
<table class="table table-bordered table-sm">
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Type</th><th>Used For</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><strong>Mountains</strong></td><td>Iron Mines, Gold Mines</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Forest</strong></td><td>Wood Cutters, Hunters</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Plains</strong></td><td>Farms, Houses, Forts, Town Centers, Warehouses, Markets, Mage Towers, Weaponsmiths, Tool Makers, Wineries, Stables, Towers</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<p>
  You gain land by <strong>exploring</strong> (send explorers from town centers) or by
  <strong>conquering</strong> it from other empires. At the start of the game, exploring is
  almost always more efficient than attacking — army upkeep is expensive and you need a
  large force to take significant land.
</p>

<h4>Getting Started</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Build <strong>Tool Makers</strong> first (5–10 is a good start) — each provides builders for construction.</li>
  <li>Build <strong>Wood Cutters</strong> and <strong>Iron Mines</strong> so you can construct more buildings.</li>
  <li>Build <strong>Town Centers</strong> to unlock explorers, thieves, catapults, and special units.</li>
  <li>Build <strong>Farms</strong> and <strong>Hunters</strong> to feed your growing population and explorers.</li>
  <li>Send <strong>explorers</strong> constantly — land is your most important resource early on.</li>
  <li>Set food ratios to <strong>High</strong> or <strong>Very High</strong> so your population grows fast.</li>
  <li>Join an <strong>alliance</strong> for protection while you build up your empire.</li>
  <li>Once you have steady income and spare land, build <strong>Mage Towers</strong> for research.</li>
  <li>Build <strong>Weapons</strong> and train <strong>Army</strong> only after you have a solid economy.</li>
</ol>

<h4>Seasons</h4>
<p>The in-game calendar affects production:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Farms</strong> only produce food during months April–October (months 4–10).</li>
  <li><strong>Winter</strong> (November–February, months 11–2): people consume wood for heating. If you run out of wood, people freeze and die.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Protection</h4>
<p>
  New players start with <strong><%= @game.settings['protection_turns'] || 200 %> turns of protection</strong>,
  during which they cannot be attacked. Use this time to build up your economy.
</p>

<h4>Scoring</h4>
<p>
  Your score reflects the total strength of your empire — resources, buildings, army, and research all contribute.
  Score also affects attack mechanics: attacking a much weaker player gives fewer victory points and suffers run penalties.
</p>
